---
// Safe to edit. The positioning line is curation-framed and carries NO project
// count, so the portfolio reads as selected work rather than a running (still
// small) total.
/* ============================================================================
   Proof Band  [revamp]
   ============================================================================
   A slim credibility beat between Act 1 (Hero) and Act 2 (Selected Work): one
   honest, specific positioning line, framed as a selection of work (no project
   count, so the page does not advertise a small running total). The "one
   person, start to finish" is the real differentiator.

   The client-name marquee that used to live here now rides the base of the hero
   (see ClientMarquee.astro, rendered at the bottom of Hero.astro), so this
   section is now just the sentence.
   ============================================================================ */
---

<section class="bg-mesh-soft bg-bg-soft py-2xl" aria-label="Studio at a glance">
  <div class="ncs-container">
    <p
      class="mx-auto max-w-[44ch] text-center text-h4 leading-[1.3] text-heading"
      data-reveal
    >
      A selection of work for churches, schools, nonprofits, and small businesses around Cincinnati,
      each project designed, built, and photographed by <span class="text-link">one person</span>,
      start to finish.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
